CHECKLIST FOR BANK EXAMS BY ANKUSH LAMBA                                      Puzzle  – 2  Ten persons A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I and J live in five storied building, which has two flats (Flat M and Flat N) on each floor. The bottommost floor is numbered as 1 and the floor immediately above it is numbered as 2 and so on. Flat N is towards the east of Flat M such that the 1st floor of flat N is towards the east of 1st floor of Flat M and so on. The dimension of each flat is same. H lives on an even numbered floor of flat N. F lives above I such that both live in the same type of flat. F does not live on the topmost floor. D does not live in Flat M. A lives adjacent to C. J lives three floors above A. A does not live on a prime numbered floor. B lives two floors above E such that B and E live in different type of flats. G lives adjacent to H. 
Puzzle  – 1  Ten boxes (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I and J) are kept on five different shelves in two different stacks viz. Stack 1 and Stack 2 which is placed to the east of Stack 1. Each stack contains five boxes kept one above another. The bottommost shelf is numbered as 1, just above it is numbered as 2 and so on till the topmost shelf is numbered as 5.  Box A is kept on an even-numbered shelf. Box G is kept immediately above box A in the same numbered stack. Box C is kept in the south-west direction of box A. Three boxes are kept between box C and box H in the same numbered stack. Box F is in west of box B but they are not kept below box A. Box I is in just north-west direction of box J. Box D is not kept below box B. 
Puzzle  – 3  Eight dishes namely Biryani, Chaat, Kheer, Dumaloo, Poha, Kachori, Daalpuri, and Imarti are placed one above another in eight different boxes, but not necessarily in the same order. The bottom-most box is numbered as 8 and the topmost box is numbered as 1. Imarti is placed immediately below Biryani but not in an even-numbered box. Kheer is placed in a prime-numbered box that is adjacent to Biryani. Poha was placed in an odd-numbered box. Only two dishes are placed between Kachori and Daalpuri. Kachori is placed in one of the boxes above Poha. Chaat is placed below Dumaloo.  
